{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Zec|13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","chapter":13,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":1,"text":"“On that day a fountain will be opened for the house of David and for the residents of Jerusalem, to wash away sin and impurity.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":2,"text":"On that day” —this is the declaration of the Lord of Armies —“I will remove the names of the idols from the land, and they will no longer be remembered. I will banish the prophets and the unclean spirit from the land.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":3,"text":"If a man still prophesies, his father and his mother who bore him will say to him, ‘You cannot remain alive because you have spoken a lie in the name of the Lord.’ When he prophesies, his father and his mother who bore him will pierce him through.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":4,"text":"On that day every prophet will be ashamed of his vision when he prophesies; they will not put on a hairy cloak in order to deceive.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":5,"text":"He will say, ‘I am not a prophet; I work the land, for a man purchased me as a servant since my youth.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":6,"text":"If someone asks him, ‘What are these wounds on your chest?’ —then he will answer, ‘I received the wounds in the house of my friends.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":7,"text":"Sword, awake against my shepherd, against the man who is my associate — Strike the shepherd, and the sheep will be scattered; I will turn my hand against the little ones.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":8,"text":"In the whole land — two-thirds will be cut off and die, but a third will be left in it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","bookOrder":37,"chapter":13,"verse":9,"text":"I will put this third through the fire; I will refine them as silver is refined and test them as gold is tested. They will call on my name, and I will answer them. I will say, ‘They are my people,’ and they will say, ‘The Lord is our God.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Zec","chapter":13,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,8,9],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"God’s People Cleansed"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":7,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":8,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":9,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Zec:13:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“On that day a fountain "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 36:9","book":"Psa","chapter":36,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 68:26","book":"Psa","chapter":68,"verse":26,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 14:27","book":"Pro","chapter":14,"verse":27,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 2:13","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 17:13","book":"Jer","chapter"